CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 26, 1946, pg. 17, reads: "Contributes to Fund - The Rev. Cornell E. Talley (right) pastor of Central Baptist Church, contributes $100 to the United electrical Workers' (local 60) strike fund at the union's headquarters in Wabash Building last week. District President T. M. Fitzpatrick accepts the check.  Others in the photo are William Harper, vice president of the Local (seated); Ben Careathers, Val Gardner, Dennis Roseberry and Edward Matthews, International representative. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Rev. Cornell Talley presenting check to T. M. Fitzpatrick, surrounded by William Harper, Ben Careathers, Val Gardner, Dennis Roseberry, and Edward Matthews, in United Electrical Workers Local 601 office, another version
